reviews.text: Ideal for a quite snack or bite. Salad, soup, fruit juice and a wide range of coffee and tea are available for your selection. Recommended for visiting when other eating places are crowded with people waiting to be served and when you are short of lapse of time to be wasted.
Air-conditioned! 29 degrees and raining outside. No brainer.

A popular fast food chain from the UK serving freshly made sandwiches, salad and hot snacks. Open for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Free Wi-Fi available. Some outlets also have AC plugs for laptops and spacious tables, ideal for working with computers and casual meeting with friends and business clients.
The place is very clean, and quiet as well. The goods are healthy enough to blend into diet plan.
Consistent food quality, but prices are far higher than I'd like. The hot wraps are good, especially the pulled pork and meatball ones, and salmon cake too. Plenty of seating too.
